task.summary:
Added slide over animation and am quite happy with how it turned out.
It fixed the button overlap bug but introduces a problem if you change pages with the menubar open. That should be a really easy fix though.

Fixed a bug where the sidebar and page contents would be out of sync when the slide animation was playing.
Buttons can no longer be pressed while an animation is playing. This will prevent future potential bugs.
Fixed a bug that would cause page contents to not line up exactly right (off by a few pixels) after the slide animation. Now it's perfect.
Probably fixed the bug that cause part of the screen to be outside the window on Windows. I don't use Windows so I really don't know it this actually fixed it, probably did though.
Started working on the login screen a bit more. Added a new GDivider class that allows placing components horizontally together and still dynamically scales and repositions things properly.

Updated the Login Screen to be more similar to the paper prototype and tested GDividers so that we can stack components both horizontally and vertically. It's pretty awesome. Changed around a bit of the colors mostly getting rid of the super ugly blue and red to the slightly less ugly dark gray and gray. Increased the account button's click area so you can now just click the name.

General improvements to menu bar UI.
* Buttons now properly center their text vertically. * Changed color scheme from shades of gray to greens. * Added drop shadow and underline to menu bar. * Sidebar backgrounds now extend to the button of the screen.
Buttons have a few new constructors that allow padding to be added around the sides of the button.
Started designing the New Project page.
Buttons can now display images on them. Added images to the placeholder buttons on the new project page. Moved the menu bar title.
